n11224"]}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to quiver, to tremble, to dither, to twitch","examples":[{"text":"جلبتُ ماءً مُثلجًا ومنفضة سجائر للمحامي الذي بدأ يقطف أوراق القات والسيجارة مشتعلة في فمه. أخذ ملء قبضته من الأغصان ورماها أمامي: «خزّن». أعدتها إليه: «ليس اليوم، سأخرج بعد قليل مع تاتيانا». اختلج فمه بانحراف لليمين.","english":"I fetched cold water and a tray for cigarettes for the lawyer who began to pluck the leaves of the qat with a cigarette in his mouth. He took a bunch of twigs and threw it before me: “Take.” I returned it: “Not today, Imma go out with Tatyana in a bit.” His mouth twitched with a tilt to the right."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to preoccupy, to possess, to cause concern","tags":["figuratively"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null}